This paper deals with the problem of lane detection, which is a common task in the field of computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper involves the use of template matching and geometric feature extraction, which are common techniques in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of unwanted noise, which is a common problem in the field of cryptography (cs.CR).
